🏗️ What is an Aggregate?

Answer:

An aggregate in NetApp is a collection of physical disks combined into a storage pool, from which volumes are created.

👉 Simple:

“Aggregate = big storage pool made of disks”

🧠 How it fits (Big Picture)
Disks → Aggregate → Volume → Data (NFS/SMB)
📦 Key Points
Built using multiple physical disks
Provides storage space for volumes
Uses RAID (data protection)
Managed at the cluster level
⚙️ Basic Commands
View aggregates
aggr show
Create aggregate
aggr create -aggregate aggr1 -diskcount 10 -raidtype raid_dp
Add disks
aggr add -aggregate aggr1 -diskcount 2
